   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <p> A <material key="marmor">white marble</material> block (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.58</measure>  × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.83</measure>, D. not measurable; these measurements were made by the <title level="m">MAMA</title> expedition), broken above (<title level="m">MAMA</title> viii wrongly describes it as broken at the right).</p>
         </div>
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
        
        <ab><lb n="1"/><rs key="acclamations" type="subject"><w lemma="εἷς">εἷς</w> <persName key="God" type="divine"><w lemma="θεός">Θεὸς</w></persName></rs><lb n="2"/><w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="μόνος">μόνος</w><lb n="3"/><w lemma="σῴζω">σῶζε</w> <persName key="constantine4" type="attested"><name nymRef="#Κωσταντεν">Κωσταντεν</name></persName>.</ab>
      </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>I. 3. The first <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ν</foreign> appears to have been cut over <term>sigma</term>. Paris and Holleaux read <foreign xml:lang="grc">Κωσταντειν</foreign>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>One God, the only one, save <persName full="yes">Konstanten</persName>!</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>See discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="VIII.17" target=".xml"/>.</p>
         </div>
